DataElement.preferredName: Unified Modeling Language Relationship Graph Edge Role Name java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A non-proprietary, third generation modelling language. The Unified Modeling Language is an open method used to specify, visualise, construct and document the artifacts of an object-oriented software-intensive system under development. The UML represents a compilation of "best engineering practices" which have proven successful in modelling large, complex systems.:A state of connectedness between people, objects, or events; to be associated or connected with something.:A connection between nodes in a graph._The usual or expected function of something; the part something plays in an action or event.:The words or language units by which a thing is known._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
